Package: garchur
Type: Package
Title: GARCH Unit Root Test with Endogenous Structural Breaks
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Muhammad", "Alkhalaf", email = "muhammedalkhalaf@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-2677-9246"))
Description: Implements the trend-GARCH(1,1) unit root test with endogenous
    structural breaks proposed by Narayan and Liu (2015)
    <doi:10.1016/j.eneco.2014.11.021>. The procedure estimates a
    mean equation with a linear trend and level-shift dummies at
    endogenously determined break dates, while allowing for
    GARCH(1,1)-type conditional heteroskedasticity in the errors.
    Up to three breaks are supported. Critical values are interpolated
    from Narayan and Liu (2015), Table III, using 50,000 Monte Carlo
    replications.
Author: Muhammad Alkhalaf [aut, cre, cph]
    (<https://orcid.org/0009-0002-2677-9246>)
